					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>124 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>305</height>
										<width>200</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>245</height>
										<width>135</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>124 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of originally 10 leaves each, signed at the beginning and at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Lacuna after folio 52.</p>
									<p>Folios 113-118 originally belonged to another manuscript of about the same date.</p>
									<p>Folios 111, 112, 119-124 are a recent addition.</p>
									<p>Water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="30" writtenLines="30">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible mastara ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Leaf catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Numerous marginal notes and additions.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script, punctuated, of the 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Maimon ben Se῾adya᾿ ben Mosheh Al-Musa᾿i (patron): inscribed, folio 110v.</p>
							<p>Folios 111-112: a calendar for the 286th and 287th cycle, followed by the series of prognostications based on the date of the teḳufot.</p>
							<p>Folios 113-118: originally a part of another manuscript: several poetical pieces and additional blessings.</p>
							<p>Folios 119r-123r: originally belonging to a different manuscript of approximately 18th century: additional prayers.</p>
							<p>Folios 122v-123r: tiḳunim.</p>
							<p>Folios 123v-124r: a table with a 292th cycle.</p>
							<p>Folio 2r: partly illegible piece similar to Kol nidre.</p>
							<p>Folio 2v: a poetical piece.</p>
							<p>Folio 3r: three additional prayers.</p>
							<p>Folio 4r: an additional prayer and the beginning of Kol nidre.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Zekhariah ben Daṿid</name>: inscribed with his name in a note, folio 1v.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Avraham ben Shalom</name>: inscribed, folio 2r.</p>
							<p>Folio 124r: two records of sale, dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1797</date> and <date calendar="Gregorian">1811</date> respectively.</p>
						</additions>
